dcterms:description: The ECMWF Reanalysis v5 (ERA5) dataset provides comprehensive global atmospheric fields, structured as a tensor with dimensions at 2.5-degree horizontal resolution, containing 66 variables. It is used for evaluating data-driven weather prediction frameworks.
dcterms:title: ECMWF Reanalysis v5 (ERA5)

dcterms:creator: J. Pathak
E. Guo
dcterms:description: FourCastNet is a high-resolution weather model utilizing the Adaptive Fourier Neural Operator (AFNO) to efficiently process input variables on a 720x1440 grid, enhancing the modeling of complex Partial Differential Equation systems.
dcterms:title: FourCastNet

dcterms:creator: T. Nguyen
dcterms:description: ClimaX is a foundation model for weather and climate, designed to enhance predictive capabilities in meteorological forecasting.
dcterms:title: ClimaX

dcterms:creator: R. Lam
dcterms:description: Pangu-Weather is a model that focuses on medium-range global weather forecasting, utilizing advanced machine learning techniques.
dcterms:title: Pangu-Weather

dcterms:creator: R. Lam
dcterms:description: GraphCast is a model that leverages graph-based learning for skillful medium-range global weather forecasting.
dcterms:title: GraphCast

dcterms:creator: C. S. Ho
dcterms:description: The lag0 and lag4x datasets are augmented datasets created using a time-sliding method to enhance the sample size for PM2.5 prediction models.
dcterms:title: lag0 and lag4x (augmented datasets)
